<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="240" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,753]" pageId="9" pageNumber="240">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,474,500]" pageId="9" pageNumber="240">Comments:</emphasis>
Between 1817 and 1831, Sellow traveled through 
<collectingCountry box="[930,998,475,501]" name="Brazil" pageId="9" pageNumber="240">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1059,1157,475,501]" name="Uruguay" pageId="9" pageNumber="240">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
collecting about 12,500 plant specimens, more than 110,000 insects (including specimens posteriorly studied by Friese), 263 mammals and 5,457 birds, plus of nests and eggs (
<bibRefCitation author="Stresemann, E." box="[557,758,547,573]" pageId="9" pageNumber="240" pagination="401 - 425" refId="ref23690" refString="Stresemann, E. (1948) Der Naturforscher Friedrich Sellow († 1831) und sein Beitrag zur Kenntnis Brasiliens. Zoologische Jahrbucher Jena Systematik, 77, 401 - 425." type="journal article" year="1948">Stresemann 1948</bibRefCitation>
). These numbers are enough to include his name among the most important naturalists who explored South America of all times (
<bibRefCitation author="Marchiori, J. N. C. &amp; Buneker, H. M. &amp; Marchiori, D. L." box="[925,1170,583,609]" pageId="9" pageNumber="240" pagination="1 - 22" refId="ref22221" refString="Marchiori, J. N. C., Buneker, H. M. &amp; Marchiori, D. L. (2018) Textos ineditos de Friedrich Sellow. 3 - Viagem pela provincia de Sao Pedro do Rio Grande do Sul (1823 - 1825). Balduinia, 61, 1 - 22. https: // doi. org / 10.5902 / 2358198032386" type="journal article" year="2018">
Marchiori 
<emphasis box="[1046,1095,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="240">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,753]" pageId="9" pageNumber="240">
Moure (1942) proposed this species (as subspecies) as junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Mocsary, 1899" authorityName="Mocsary" authorityYear="1899" box="[1018,1299,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="240" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis box="[1018,1037,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="240">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1049,1127,619,644]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="240">minuta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mocsary, A." box="[1133,1299,619,645]" pageId="9" pageNumber="240" pagination="251 - 255" refId="ref22382" refString="Mocsary, A. (1899) Species novae generis Centris Fabr. in collectione Musaei Nationalis Hungarici. Termeszetrajzi Fuzetek, 22, 251 - 255." type="journal article" year="1899">Mocsáry, 1899</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fabricius, 1804))" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1804" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="240" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="analis">
<emphasis box="[1336,1355,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="240">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1368,1436,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="240">analis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fabricius, J. C." box="[159,339,655,681]" pageId="9" pageNumber="240" refId="ref21628" refString="Fabricius, J. C. (1804) Systema Piezatorum secundum ordines, genera, species, adjectis synonymis, locis, observationibus, de- scriptionibus. Reichard, Brunsvigae, 439 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 10490" type="book" year="1804">Fabricius, 1804</bibRefCitation>
))
</taxonomicName>
. Nevertheless, both species are quite different. One of the easiest characters that can be used to differentiate them is the presence of orange, long and simple setae on the lower corner of the pronotum, present in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1804" box="[151,252,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="240" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="analis">
<emphasis box="[151,170,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="240">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[184,252,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="240">analis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and absent in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1899" box="[414,533,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="240" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis box="[414,433,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="240">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[447,533,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="240">simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
